sec.p:
We presented the numerical results for a small population (
N = 4
) because the stochastic effects are magnified in a small population and, therefore, using the stochastic version of the SI model makes more sense for a small population. As a matter of fact, the stochastic and the deterministic versions of the SI model converge for relatively large populations (although the deterministic version still fails to give a closed-form solution for a non-continuous or non-differentiable contact rate as a function of the number of infectives). Nevertheless, all the theoretical results remain valid for any size of the population.
